abstract.value: Chloe Faith Dzubilo was an artist and AIDS and transgender activist. The Chloe Faith Dzubilo Papers comprise art, photographs, writing, annotated books, various annotated paper materials, journals, correspondence, articles, flyers, invitations, posters, brochures, objects, and audiovisual materials. The papers document Dzubilo's life as an artist, and a transgender woman living with HIV/AIDS while advocating for the rights and representation of people with HIV/AIDS and the transgender community.

p.value: Materials are open to researchers. Please contact the Fales Library and Special Collections, fales.library@nyu.edu, 212-998-2596.

Series I: Artwork2756202004-2010Scope and Content

This series contains artwork created by Dzubilo using various mediums on paper and cloth. Majority of the work relates to life or advocacy for people with HIV/AIDS and transgender people. Some art also is either created with or about Dzubilo's partner T De Long.

Arrangement

Series I is arranged alphabetically by title of the artwork. If there is no title, the folders are arranged chronologically.

This series contains both professional and personal photographs of Dzubilo, her family, and friends. Alice O'Malley and Katrina del Mar frequently photographed Dzubilo, and their work can be found throughout the series. Dzubilo's noted can also be found on the back of most photographs.

Arrangement

Series II is arranged in original order the photographs were found in the collection.

Professional and Personal Photographs2756481983-2004ASeries III: Writing2756221988-2010Scope and Content

This series contains both poetry and short stories written by Dzubilo as well as her personal correspondence. Binder #1 and the folders of its contents contains poetry, stories, notebooks, correspondence, and Equi-Aid material written by Dzubilo. Cover letters and recommendation letters can also be found in this series.
